title: Jordan Producer Prices
description: Producer Prices in Jordan decreased to 143.60 points in September from 145.40 points in August of 2022. Producer Prices in Jordan averaged 108.94 points from 2002 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 173.40 points in August of 2008 and a record low of 59.10 points in April of 2002. In Jordan, the Producer Price Index measures the average change in price of goods and services sold by manufacturers and producers in the wholesale market during a given period. This page provides - Jordan Producer Prices - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Department of Statistics, Jordan
